<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
9. 
<taxonomicName LSID="17D65FA5-0F89-5EF0-AFF1-7791C5A44AC6" authority="(Kunth) G. Don, Hort. Brit. [Loudon]: 98 (1830)." authorityName="G. Don, Hort. Brit. [Loudon]: 98" authorityYear="1830" baseAuthorityName="Kunth" family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. maypurensis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="maypurensis">M. maypurensis (Kunth) G.Don, Hort. Brit. [Loudon]: 98 (1830).</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Microteaceae" genus="Ancistrocarpus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ancistrocarpus maypurensis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maypurensis">Ancistrocarpus maypurensis</taxonomicName>
Kunth, Nov. Gen. Sp. [quarto] 2: 186 (1817). Lectotype (Sennikov &amp; Sukhorukov, designated here): COLOMBIA. &quot;In pratis Maypure&quot;, ex herb. Bonpland, ex herb. Kunth s.n. (B 10 0296283!). Note: Kunth, who revised the main set of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Humboldt’s">Humboldt's</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Bonpland’s">Bonpland's</normalizedToken>
collections at P, acquired a large part of this herbarium. After his death, the collections were transferred to the Botanical Museum in Berlin (
<bibRefCitation author="Urban, I" journalOrPublisher="Jahrbuch des Koeniglichen botanischen Gartens und des botanischen Museums zu Berlin" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="1 - 164" refId="B56" refString="Urban, I, 1881. Geschichte des Koeniglichen botanischen Gartens und des Koeniglichen Herbariums zu Berlin, nebst einer Darstellung des augenblicklichen Zustandes dieser Institute. Jahrbuch des Koeniglichen botanischen Gartens und des botanischen Museums zu Berlin 1: 1 - 164" title="Geschichte des Koeniglichen botanischen Gartens und des Koeniglichen Herbariums zu Berlin, nebst einer Darstellung des augenblicklichen Zustandes dieser Institute." volume="1" year="1881">Urban 1881</bibRefCitation>
), where they partly survived.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName authority="J.A.Schultes, 1820" authorityName="Humb. &amp; Bonpl. ex Roem &amp; Schult" authorityYear="1820" baseAuthorityName="Kunth" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Microteaceae" genus="Ceratococca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ceratococca maypurensis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maypurensis">Ceratococca maypurensis</taxonomicName>
Humb. &amp; Bonpl. ex Roem. &amp; Schult., Syst. Veg., ed. 15, 6: 800 (1820). Holotype: Colombia. Maypure, Cataracta, Orinoco, A.J.A. Bonpland &amp; F.W.H.A. von Humboldt s.n. (B-W 06266-01!). Notes: 
<taxonomicName authority="J.A.Schultes, 1820" authorityName="Humb. &amp; Bonpl. ex Roem &amp; Schult" authorityYear="1820" baseAuthorityName="Kunth" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Microteaceae" genus="Ceratococca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ceratococca maypurensis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maypurensis">Ceratococca maypurensis</taxonomicName>
was apparently based on a duplicate of the collection on which 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Microteaceae" genus="Ancistrocarpus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ancistrocarpus maypurensis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maypurensis">Ancistrocarpus maypurensis</taxonomicName>
was described earlier by Kunth. However, a specimen in the Herbarium of Willdenow was not accessible to Kunth at the time when the protologue was prepared (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/1217774" author="McVaugh, R" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="78 - 86" refId="B32" refString="McVaugh, R, 1955. The American collections of Humboldt and Bonpland, as described in the Systema Vegetabilium of Roemer and Schultes. Taxon 4 (4): 78 - 86, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/1217774" title="The American collections of Humboldt and Bonpland, as described in the Systema Vegetabilium of Roemer and Schultes." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/1217774" volume="4" year="1955">McVaugh 1955</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Microteaceae" genus="Potamophila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Potamophila parviflora" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parviflora">Potamophila parviflora</taxonomicName>
Schrank, Pl. Rar. Horti Monac. 2: tab. 63 (1821), nom. illegit., non R.Br. 1810.
</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Microteaceae" genus="Ancistrocarpus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ancistrocarpus schrankii" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schrankii">Ancistrocarpus schrankii</taxonomicName>
Ledeb., Index Seminum Horti Academici Dorpatensis 1821 (Appendix I): 21 (1821). Described on the basis of plants cultivated in the Botanical Garden in Munich. Lectotype (Sennikov &amp; Sukhorukov, designated here): [icon] fig. 63 in 
<bibRefCitation author="Schrank, F" journalOrPublisher="14, pt. 2. Fleischner, Leipzig" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" refId="B42" refString="Schrank, F, 1821. Plantae rariores Horti academici Monacensis, Vol. 2. Venditur in Instituto lithographico Scholae festivalis, Berlin." title="Plantae rariores Horti academici Monacensis, Vol. 2. Venditur in Instituto lithographico Scholae festivalis, Berlin." year="1821">Schrank (1821)</bibRefCitation>
. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Lectotype of Ancistrocarpus schrankii (fig. 63 in Schrank, 1821). Image provided by the library of Biological Faculty, Lomonosov Moscow State University." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.115.29041.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/255675" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">22</figureCitation>
). Note: 
<bibRefCitation author="von Ledebour, CF" journalOrPublisher="Jahrbuch des Koeniglichen botanischen Gartens und des botanischen Museums zu Berlin" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" refId="B59" refString="von Ledebour, CF, 1821. Indicis seminum Horti Academici Dorpatensis (Appendix I). J.C.Schuenmann, Dorpat." title="Indicis seminum Horti Academici Dorpatensis (Appendix I). J. C. Schuenmann, Dorpat." year="1821">von Ledebour (1821)</bibRefCitation>
intended (Art. 6.11) to introduce his new species name as a replacement name for the later homonym published by Schrank, and both names are therefore necessarily homotypic. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schrank, F" journalOrPublisher="14, pt. 2. Fleischner, Leipzig" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" refId="B42" refString="Schrank, F, 1821. Plantae rariores Horti academici Monacensis, Vol. 2. Venditur in Instituto lithographico Scholae festivalis, Berlin." title="Plantae rariores Horti academici Monacensis, Vol. 2. Venditur in Instituto lithographico Scholae festivalis, Berlin." year="1821">Schrank (1821)</bibRefCitation>
published his new species names based on seeds sent or brought from Brazil by C.F. von Martius. Original herbarium collections of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Microteaceae" genus="Potamophila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Potamophila parviflora" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parviflora">Potamophila parviflora</taxonomicName>
Schrank were not found at M and most likely had never been prepared (H.-J. Esser, pers. comm. 2018), and the illustration published as part of the protologue is the only original element available for lectotypification (Art. 9.4). The protologue of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Microteaceae" genus="Potamophila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Potamophila parviflora" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parviflora">Potamophila parviflora</taxonomicName>
indicates that the new species has five styles (although only three are visible in the accompanying illustration) and a pericarp with setae. Coupled with pedicellate flowers and petiolate leaves, easily recognizable in the illustration, these characters are indicative of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Microteaceae" genus="Microtea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Microtea maypurensis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maypurensis">
<pageBreakToken pageId="31" pageNumber="32" start="start">Microtea</pageBreakToken>
maypurensis
</taxonomicName>
, of which 
<taxonomicName family="Microteaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. parviflora" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species" species="parviflora">P. parviflora</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Microteaceae" genus="Ancistrocarpus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ancistrocarpus schrankii" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schrankii">Ancistrocarpus schrankii</taxonomicName>
) is a later synonym. This agrees with the conclusions of 
<bibRefCitation author="Moquin-Tandon, A" editor="De Candolle, A" journalOrPublisher="13, pt. 2. V. Masson, Paris" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="3 - 40" refId="B34" refString="Moquin-Tandon, A, 1849. Phytolaccaceae. In: De Candolle, A, Ed., Prodromus systematis universalis regni vegetabilis, Vol. 13, pt. 2. V. Masson, Paris: 3 - 40" title="Phytolaccaceae." volumeTitle="Prodromus systematis universalis regni vegetabilis, Vol." year="1849">Moquin-Tandon (1849)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Walter, H" journalOrPublisher="Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie (Beiblatt)" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" refId="B61" refString="Walter, H, 1909. Phytolaccaceae. In: Engler A (Ed.) Das Pflanzenreich, Heft 39. Wilhelm Engelmann, Leipzig." title="Phytolaccaceae. In: Engler A (Ed.) Das Pflanzenreich, Heft 39. Wilhelm Engelmann, Leipzig." year="1909">Walter (1909)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/2395128" author="Nowicke, WH" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="294 - 364" refId="B37" refString="Nowicke, WH, 1968. Palynotaxonomic study of the Phytolaccaceae. Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 55 (3): 294 - 364, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/2395128" title="Palynotaxonomic study of the Phytolaccaceae." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/2395128" volume="55" year="1968">Nowicke (1968)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schrank, F" journalOrPublisher="14, pt. 2. Fleischner, Leipzig" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" refId="B42" refString="Schrank, F, 1821. Plantae rariores Horti academici Monacensis, Vol. 2. Venditur in Instituto lithographico Scholae festivalis, Berlin." title="Plantae rariores Horti academici Monacensis, Vol. 2. Venditur in Instituto lithographico Scholae festivalis, Berlin." year="1821">Schrank (1821)</bibRefCitation>
stated that the new species was collected in &quot;Brasilia prope sinum Omnium Sanctorum ad flumina locis umbrosis&quot;. There is a gathering, Herb. Martius 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">2198</emphasis>
(M 0274659, M 0274661, M 0274662), which was collected by Martius in Bahia, Cachoeira, along the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Paraguaçu">Paraguacu</normalizedToken>
River at the distance of ca. 35 km from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Baía">Baia</normalizedToken>
de Todos os Santos (Bay of All Saints), in December 1818 (see the route of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Martius’">Martius'</normalizedToken>
expedition in 
<bibRefCitation author="Tiefenbacher, L" journalOrPublisher="PhytoKeys" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" refId="B54" refString="Tiefenbacher, L, 1983. Die Brasilienexpedition von J. B. v. Spix und C. F. Ph. v. Martius in den Jahren 1817 bis 1820. Spixiana 9(Supplement): 35-42." title="Die Brasilienexpedition von J. B. v. Spix und C. F. Ph. v. Martius in den Jahren 1817 bis 1820. Spixiana 9 (Supplement): 35 - 42." year="1983">Tiefenbacher (1983)</bibRefCitation>
). This is the likely type locality of 
<taxonomicName family="Microteaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. parviflora" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species" species="parviflora">P. parviflora</taxonomicName>
, and the gathering may be the voucher for the seed collection sent by Martius to the Munich Botanical Garden. The plants of this gathering are unmistakeably referable to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Don, Hort. Brit. [Loudon]: 98" authorityYear="1830" baseAuthorityName="Kunth" family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. maypurensis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species" species="maypurensis">M. maypurensis</taxonomicName>
. Two other specimens, Herb. Martius 2309 (M 0274665, M 0274666), collected by Martius in Bahia, Monte Santo, in April 1819, were mistakingly labelled as 
<taxonomicName family="Microteaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. parviflora" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species" species="parviflora">P. parviflora</taxonomicName>
. They clearly disagree with the protologue and belong to 
<taxonomicName family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. celosioides" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species" species="celosioides">M. celosioides</taxonomicName>
. This curatorial mislabelling probably occurred because of the confusingly similar localities on its label and in the protologue.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicName family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. sprengelii" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species" species="sprengelii">M. sprengelii</taxonomicName>
Moq. in DC., Prodr. 13(2): 19 (1849). Neotype (Sennikov &amp; Sukhorukov, designated here): BRAZIL. Bahia, Rio Belmonte, [Aug. 1816], 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Maximilian, Prinz zu Wied 53</emphasis>
(BR000005537679, image!). Note: 
<bibRefCitation author="Moquin-Tandon, A" editor="De Candolle, A" journalOrPublisher="13, pt. 2. V. Masson, Paris" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="3 - 40" refId="B34" refString="Moquin-Tandon, A, 1849. Phytolaccaceae. In: De Candolle, A, Ed., Prodromus systematis universalis regni vegetabilis, Vol. 13, pt. 2. V. Masson, Paris: 3 - 40" title="Phytolaccaceae." volumeTitle="Prodromus systematis universalis regni vegetabilis, Vol." year="1849">Moquin-Tandon (1849)</bibRefCitation>
based the protologue of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moq" authorityYear="1849" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Microteaceae" genus="Microtea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Microtea sprengelii" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sprengelii">Microtea sprengelii</taxonomicName>
entirely on the description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Don, Hort. Brit. [Loudon]: 98" authorityYear="1830" baseAuthorityName="Kunth" family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. maypurensis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species" species="maypurensis">M. maypurensis</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Sprengel, K" journalOrPublisher="American Journal of Botany" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" refId="B45" refString="Sprengel, K, 1820. Neue Entdeckungen im ganzen Umfang der Pflanzenkunde, Vol. 1. F.Fleischer, Leipzig, 1-154." title="Neue Entdeckungen im ganzen Umfang der Pflanzenkunde, Vol. 1. F. Fleischer, Leipzig, 1 - 154." year="1820">Sprengel (1820)</bibRefCitation>
. He stressed the diagnostic character of opposite leaves, which is almost impossible in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Microteaceae" genus="Microtea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Microtea" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Microtea</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sprengel’s">Sprengel's</normalizedToken>
description closely matches the characters of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Don, Hort. Brit. [Loudon]: 98" authorityYear="1830" baseAuthorityName="Kunth" family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. maypurensis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species" species="maypurensis">M. maypurensis</taxonomicName>
except for the opposite leaves, and unlikely belongs to any other species. 
<bibRefCitation author="Moquin-Tandon, A" editor="De Candolle, A" journalOrPublisher="13, pt. 2. V. Masson, Paris" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="3 - 40" refId="B34" refString="Moquin-Tandon, A, 1849. Phytolaccaceae. In: De Candolle, A, Ed., Prodromus systematis universalis regni vegetabilis, Vol. 13, pt. 2. V. Masson, Paris: 3 - 40" title="Phytolaccaceae." volumeTitle="Prodromus systematis universalis regni vegetabilis, Vol." year="1849">Moquin-Tandon (1849)</bibRefCitation>
assumed a technical error in 
<bibRefCitation author="Sprengel, K" journalOrPublisher="American Journal of Botany" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" refId="B45" refString="Sprengel, K, 1820. Neue Entdeckungen im ganzen Umfang der Pflanzenkunde, Vol. 1. F.Fleischer, Leipzig, 1-154." title="Neue Entdeckungen im ganzen Umfang der Pflanzenkunde, Vol. 1. F. Fleischer, Leipzig, 1 - 154." year="1820">Sprengel (1820)</bibRefCitation>
, with which we agree. Sprengel noted specifically that he based the description on plants from Brazil. No relevant specimens survived. As a neotype, we designate a specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Don, Hort. Brit. [Loudon]: 98" authorityYear="1830" baseAuthorityName="Kunth" family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. maypurensis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species" species="maypurensis">M. maypurensis</taxonomicName>
collected in Brazil by Prinz Maximilian, a contemporary collection that may have been available to Sprengel.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicName family="Microteaceae" form="lanceolata" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" infraspecific-rank="f." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. glochidiata" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="form" species="glochidiata">M. glochidiata f. lanceolata</taxonomicName>
Chodat &amp; Hassler, Bull. Herb. Boiss., ser. 2, 3: 418 (1903). Lectotype (Sennikov &amp; Sukhorukov, designated here): Paraguay. Ad marginem silvae [prope] Caraguatay, Aug.[ust] [1897], 
